abstract: SCHENECTADY, N.Y., March 7.--The body of an unknown well dressed man was found in a hog pen on George White's farm in Rotterdam, about four miles from this place, last night. It is supposed that the man was frozen to death. When the pigs were fed yesterday morning the man was not in the pen. The remains were brought to this city today. They are not mutilated. Their is no clue to their identity.

abstract: FARGO, Dakota, March 12.--Passenger train No. 1 on the Northern Pacific Railway this morning came into collision with freight No. 16, four miles west of Wheatland. A brakeman and the baggagemaster were also seriously injured. It is understood that no passengers were injured.

abstract: EAU CLAIRE, Wis., March 12.--A dastardly attempt was made last evening to wreck a Chicago, Milwaukee and St. Paul passenger train near here. Some miscreant broke the lock and moved a switch at Breen's Crossing, sending the entire train from the track.
